Former ANN7 news editor Rajesh Sundaram back on stand at Zondo Commission. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former SABC employee, Josias Johannes Scott took the stand at the state capture inquiry on Tuesday. Former ANN7 editor, Rajesh Sundaram concluded his testimony at the state capture inquiry earlier. He told the commission Atul Gupta would often brag about how much his family was in control of the South African government. On Monday Sundaram, detailed how closely involved former president Jacob Zuma was in setting up the 24-hour news channel. READ: Former ANN7 editor details Zuma's alleged role in the channel The Indian national claims he was lured to the Gupta-owned TV news station under false pretences. Sundaram claims he attended three meetings regarding ANN7 with Zuma and others.